section.section:
Notwithstanding any other law, a person may not serve as a fiduciary if the person has been convicted of:
a felony;
a misdemeanor involving moral turpitude;
a violation of this subtitle;
a conspiracy or attempt to commit a crime described under item (i), (ii), or (iii) of this paragraph; or
a crime in which a crime described under item (i), (ii), (iii), or (iv) of this paragraph is an element.
